{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "12", "m": "11", "Y": "2025"}, "time": {"H": "12", "M": "19", "S": "59"}}, "news": [{"title": "Avoidance transactions under IBC: What happens after insolvency resolution?", "para": "Indian insolvency law now allows recovery of assets from unfair transactions even after a company's resolution process ends.  Courts and new regulations confirm that legal actions to reverse preferential or fraudulent deals can continue. This strengthens the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code's aim to protect creditors and maximize value.  Recovered funds will benefit stakeholders.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/blog/understanding-the-continuation-of-avoidance-transactions-post-ibc-resolution/125270055?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-69340/125270055.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "understanding-the-continuation-of-avoidance-transactions-post-ibc-resolution"}, {"title": "Asian Paints' net profit rises 46.79% in Q2 FY26", "para": "Asian Paints reported a significant 46.79% surge in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, reaching \u20b91,018.23 crore. This growth was driven by a robust 10.9% volume increase in its domestic decorative business, despite monsoon challenges. The company also saw a 6.45% rise in total income to \u20b98,729.91 crore.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/paints/asian-paints-reports-4679-surge-in-q2-fy26-profit/125271733?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-15156/125271733.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "paints"}, {"title": "Ahmedabad: Demolition drive targets illegal constructions in Vatva, Jamalpur", "para": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation's TDO led demolition drives in Vatva and Jamalpur, clearing 14 illegal structures encroaching on Bhoja Talav and a leased plot. Additionally, two toilet